<li id="comment-23115" class="comment byuser comment-author-sethc bypostauthor odd alt depth-2">
    <div class="comment-body" id="div-comment-23115">
        <div class="comment-author avatar">
    <img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/79067e3be1142bf98e26a69f3145ca94?s=64&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D64&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-64 photo' height='64' width='64' />
        </div>

        <div class="comment-meta commentdata">

    <cite class="fn">sethc</cite><br/>

            <div class="comment-meta-data">

    Published May 26, 2013  4:13 pm <span class="meta-sep"></span> <a href="#comment-23115" class="permalink" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a> 
            </div>
        <p>Tari, thanks for the suggestion.  Because of the circumstances we received the donations under, I only feel comfortable using them for tips.  My original statement was that we would use the donations for that purpose.  So, using them for something else just wouldn&#8217;t feel right to me.  I can&#8217;t know if the people who donated would want that or not.  So instead, mom and I have happily given to homeless in Aaron&#8217;s name, from our own pockets.  Thanks for writing!</p>

            <div class="reply">
    <div class="comment-reply-link"><a class='comment-reply-link' href='/?p=20&#038;replytocom=23115#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-23115", "23115", "respond", "20")'>Reply</a></div>            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</li>
    </li>
</ul>
