    Published July 14, 2012  6:24 pm <span class="meta-sep"></span> <a href="#comment-1278" class="permalink" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a> 
            </div>
        <p>A true Buddhist would not say anything in reply to Jerry, but I&#8217;m far from reaching enlightenment.  Jerry&#8217;s post is despicable.  He&#8217;s as far from Jesus as I am from enlightenment.  We both have something in common.  It&#8217;s called Limbo in Catholicism, which I have happily dropped.  He could have said pray Jesus will help you, but instead he said Jesus is the only path.  I hate to disabuse you of your false thought, but Jesus is not the only path to God.  There are many.  Go to any AA meeting in the world, and you will find God (Group of drunks).  The new initiate at AA sometimes has to look at the group for a higher power, and it&#8217;s just as good as your notion of Jesus.  Jerry is pathetic.  He is every reason this country has separation of state and religion.  Can you imagine Jerry&#8217;s world if we didn&#8217;t?  That&#8217;s right Jerry, we would be as despicable as the Taliban.  In short, Jerry, I challenge you to renounce your ignorant dogma and audit or take a class in Eastern Religion at a local college.  There you will start to learn there are other paths.  Then maybe I can call you human.</p>

