        <p>To Kent</p>
<p>About your &#8220;Sad Life Story&#8221;,<br />
you have led a &#8220;VERY EASY&#8221; Life,<br />
IF that is the Best that you can do.</p>
<p>I Do NOT think my Life, has been/is that bad,<br />
But IS FAR WORSE than what you described.</p>
<p>Yes, WAS Qualified as an EMT.<br />
Yes, Had a Full time Job.<br />
Yes, Had some Savings.<br />
Yes, Had several Friends.<br />
Yes, Was in GOOD Physical Condition.<br />
Often Drove Vehicles &amp;<br />
 had Accumulated OVER 2 MILLION Miles.<br />
(Notice How ALL ARE in PAST Tense !!)<br />
Then one Afternoon, that was all to Change !</p>
<p>Finished working for the day;<br />
Got home (By Bicycle as Usual);<br />
Went to go to Bank and Cash my Paycheck;<br />
AND<br />
Awoke in HOSPITAL 3 DAYS Later !!</p>
<p>Another 4 Days Later (Week from last day worked),<br />
Parents &#8220;Removed&#8221; me from Hospital,<br />
as my condition was Stable<br />
(Showed NO Sign of Getting Worse or Better).</p>
<p>Now:<br />
Unemployed;<br />
OWE LOTS of MONEY;<br />
IN POOR Physical Health;<br />
NOT ALLOWED to use ANY of EMT Training;<br />
NOT ALLOWED to Drive;<br />
and More.</p>
<p>Occasionally, funds are SO Short,<br />
that NEED to use Local FOOD Banks.<br />
Compared to Many of the Homeless that<br />
REGULARLY NEED these Food Banks,<br />
I AM STILL Living in Luxury !!</p>

