        <p>Recently, while working in a Coffee Shop, Received a Nice Tip !!<br />
Normally, Total of ALL Tips is about $2.50 Per Person, PER SHIFT !<br />
Once got a $50.00 Tip !</p>
<p>While working the Night Shift,<br />
there OFTEN was JUST Me (the &#8216;Server&#8217;) and the &#8216;Baker&#8217; !<br />
Because the &#8216;Baker&#8217; Earned SO MUCH MORE than me,<br />
the &#8216;Baker&#8217; often let me have ALL Tips. </p>
<p>One Evening, a Fairly Regular Customer, Left a $50.00 Tip !<br />
(The Tip alone, was a $50.00 bill !)<br />
Normally, CAN NOT ACCEPT Bills LARGER than $20.00,<br />
UNLESS a Manager CAN VALIDATE the Bill !</p>
<p>Since this Bill was ENTIRELY for the TIP, I Could Accept IT,<br />
&amp; OFFERED to find ways to get 1/2 or $25.00 to the &#8216;Baker&#8217; !<br />
The &#8216;Baker&#8217; still Refused to take any of the Tips<br />
( part of the $50 or any of the other tips).</p>
<p>Much Thanks to the &#8216;Baker&#8217; and the Customer,<br />
this ONE Tip,<br />
was MORE than I Normally MADE in a SINGLE NIGHT !</p>

